  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 663 (sk3241): __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__ dict-presence checks for socket types."
    - "Theme: __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ dict-presence (reflected division/modulo)."
    - "All values False — hash objects, UUID, Struct, and socket types have no reflected division/modulo protocol."
    - "socket.socket is a Python class; it does not define __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, or __rmod__ in its __dict__."
    - "socket.AddressFamily and socket.SocketKind are IntEnum subclasses (EnumType metaclass)."
    - "AddressFamily and SocketKind are IntEnum but do NOT define __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, or __rmod__ in their own __dict__; these methods are not overridden at the subclass level."
    - "operator.contains(socket.AddressFamily.__dict__, '__rtruediv__') is False — not present in AddressFamily's own __dict__."
    - "operator.contains(socket.SocketKind.__dict__, '__rtruediv__') is False — same reasoning as AddressFamily."
    - "All values are False for all 3 socket types across all 3 operators."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

